1 33. "Moderate sedation" means a drug-induced depression of
2 consciousness during which patients respond purposefully to verbal
3 commands, either alone or accompanied by light tactile stimulation.
4 No interventions are required to maintain a patent airway, and
5 spontaneous ventilation is adequate. Cardiovascular function is
6 usually maintained;
7 34. "Prophylaxis" means the removal of any and all calcareous
