4 Section 328.29a. A. The following acts or occurrences by a
5 dental assistant shall constitute grounds for which the penalties
6 specified in Section 328.44a of this title may be imposed by the
7 Board of Dentistry or be the basis for denying a new applicant any
8 license or permit issued by the Board:
9 1. Any of the causes now existing in the laws of this state;
10 2. A violation of the provisions of the State Dental Act; or
11 3. A violation of the rules of the Board promulgated pursuant
12 to the State Dental Act.
13 B. The Board shall also have the power to act upon a petition
14 by a dental assistant for reinstatement to good standing. The Board
15 shall keep a record of the evidence and proceedings in all matters
16 involving the revocation or suspension of a permit, censure or
17 probation of a dental assistant. The Board shall make findings of
18 fact and a decision thereon. Notification of the licensee or permit
19 holder shall occur pursuant to Section 328.21 of this title.
20 C. The decision shall be final unless the dental assistant
21 appeals the decision as provided by the State Dental Act.
22 D. The Board shall have power to revoke or suspend the permit,
23 censure, or place on probation a dental assistant for a violation of
24 one or more of the following:
Req. No. 16791 Page 38

1 1. Pleading guilty or nolo contendere to, or being convicted
2 of, a felony crime that substantially relates to the occupation of a
3 dental assistant and poses a reasonable threat to public safety, or
4 a violation of federal or state controlled dangerous substances
5 laws;
6 2. Presenting to the Board a false application or documentation
7 for a permit;
8 3. Being, by reason of persistent inebriety or addiction to
9 drugs, incompetent to continue to function as a dental assistant;
10 4. Functioning outside the general direct or direct visual
11 supervision of a dentist for a procedure required by this act;
12 5. Performing any function prohibited by Chapter 15 of the
13 Oklahoma Administrative Code or any violation that would be a
14 violation for a dentist or hygienist under Section 328.32 or 328.33
15 of this title, or any other duty not assignable to a dental
16 assistant; or
17 6. Failure to secure an annual registration as specified in
18 Section 328.41 of this title.
19 E. The Board's review panel, as set forth in Section 328.43a of
20 this title, upon concurrence with the president of the Board, may
21 determine that an emergency exists to temporarily suspend the permit
22 of a dental assistant if the panel finds that public health, safety
23 or welfare imperatively requires emergency action. The panel may
24
Req. No. 16791 Page 39

1 cond uct a hearing pursuant to Section 314 of Title 75 of the
2 Oklahoma Statutes for the temporary suspension.
3 F. As used in this section:
4 1. "Substantially relates" means the nature of criminal conduct
5 for which the person was convicted has a direct bearing on the
6 fitness or ability to perform one or more of the duties or
7 responsibilities necessarily related to the occupation; and
8 2. "Poses a reasonable threat" means the nature of criminal
9 conduct for which the person was convicted involved an act or threat
