20 Section 328.31b. A. Every dental office or treatment facility,
21 whether individual, group or multi-doctor practice operating under a
22 name, trade name or other professional entity shall maintain written
23 records on each patient treated at the facility and shall make these
24 records available to the Board of Dentistry and other regulatory
Req. No. 16791 Page 41

1 enti ties or be subject to the penalties as set forth in Section
2 328.44a of this title.
3 B. Each licensed dentist shall maintain written records on each
4 patient that shall contain, at a minimum, the following information
5 about the patient:
6 1. A current health history listing known illnesses, other
7 treating physicians and current medications prescribed;
8 2. Results of a clinical examination, including a physical
9 intraoral examination and head and neck examination, tests
10 conducted, and any lab results including the identification, or lack
11 thereof, of any oral pathology or diseases;
12 3. Treatment plan proposed by the dentist; and
13 4. Treatment rendered to the patient. The patient record shall
14 clearly identify the dentist and the dental hygienist or dental
15 assistant providing the treatment with the dentist, specialty or
16 dental hygienist license number. The patient record shall include
17 documentation of any medications prescribed, administered or
18 dispensed to the patient.
19 C. Prior to a dentist prescribing, diagnosing, or overseeing
20 patient treatment for any dental appliance, the patient shall be a
21 patient of record and the dentist shall conduct an in-person patient
22 examination.
23 D. 1. The name of the dentist or dentists actually providing
24 the dental services to the patient shall appear on all insurance
Req. No. 16791 Page 42

1 clai m forms, billing invoices, or statements sent to the patient and
2 on all receipts if any are given to the patient.
3 2. Treatment records shall be maintained for each patient that
4 clearly identify the dentist or dentists, hygienists or dental
5 assistants who performed all dental services for the patient.
6 E. Whenever patient records are released or transferred, the
7 dentist releasing or transferring the records shall maintain either
8 the original records or copies thereof and a notation shall be made
9 in the retained records indicating to whom the records were released
10 or transferred.
11 F. All claims being submitted for insurance must be signed,
12 stamped or have an electronic signature by the treating dentist.
13 G. Patient records may be kept in an electronic data format,
14 provided that the dentist maintains a backup copy of information
15 stored in the data processing system using disk, tape or other
16 electronic back-up system and that backup is updated on a regular
17 basis, at least weekly, to assure that data is not lost due to
18 system failure. Any electronic data system shall be capable of
19 producing a hard copy on demand.
20 H. All patient records shall be maintained for seven (7) years
21 from the date of treatment.
22 I. Each licensed dentist shall retain a copy of each entry in
23 his or her patient appointment book, calendar, or such other log,
24 calendar, book, file or computer data used in lieu of an appointment
