9 Section 328.34. A. A dental hygienist may practice dental
10 hygiene under the supervision of a dentist in a dental office or
11 treatment facility. A dentist may employ not more than the
12 equivalent of three full-time dental hygienists for each dentist
13 actively practicing in the same dental office. Employing the
14 equivalent of three dental hygienists shall mean the employment or
15 any combination of full- or part-time dental hygienists not to
16 exceed one hundred twenty (120) hours per week per dentist.
17 B. 1. A dentist may delegate to a dental hygienist the
18 following procedures:
19 a. the duties and expanded duties authorized for dental
20 assistants by the State Dental Act or the rules of the
21 Board of Dentistry,
22 b. health history assessment pertaining to dental
23 hygiene,
24
